race.comment: Terrific maiden and any one of a half a dozen here wouldn't shock but you have to stay with SWOBODA (14). Resumed with a near miss at Ararat then tackled a BM74 in town and ran last but was only two lengths from the winner. Drops many classes for this back to maiden grade and drawn for a soft run. Looks tough to stop. CLEVOR TREVER (3) was well in the market on debut and sat fourth and kept coming to just miss. Drawn for a good run and doesn't have to improve much for this. ASAKURA (1) was a near miss on debut then given another break. Has been gelded, fitter for a hit-out and rates among the top chances here fresh.  GASOLINE RAINBOW (11) led and was swamped late here on debut. Further improved and off the low draw expecting a bold sight again.
